WEBVTT

00:10.595 --> 00:14.182
<i>[soft jazz music]</i>

00:14.182 --> 00:21.189
<i>♪ ♪</i>

00:34.160 --> 00:35.578
<i>[bell dings]</i>

00:35.578 --> 00:42.585
<i>♪ ♪</i>

01:14.200 --> 01:17.829
[crickets chirping]

01:17.829 --> 01:19.622
CHILD:
Throw it, throw it!

01:19.622 --> 01:20.665
[egg splats]

01:20.665 --> 01:23.585
[laughter]

01:23.585 --> 01:24.919
Throw it!

01:40.268 --> 01:42.354
[bike bell rings]

01:42.354 --> 01:44.356
[distant train horn blares]

02:03.792 --> 02:05.502
- Mrs. Gore, I didn't even--

02:05.502 --> 02:06.544
[hand slams on desk]

02:10.173 --> 02:15.804
- Mrs. Gore, you gave
your entire class detention?

02:17.597 --> 02:22.519
- Well, one of them was
behind this, I'm sure of it.

02:25.897 --> 02:29.025
- Do you know
how many calls I'm fielding?

02:29.025 --> 02:30.777
And it is not like this
is the first time

02:30.777 --> 02:32.195
you have done
something along these--

02:32.195 --> 02:36.825
- Earl--Mr. Albert--these kids,

02:36.825 --> 02:40.662
like all of us,
are a part of a community.

02:40.662 --> 02:43.540
The actions
of one affect us all.

02:43.540 --> 02:46.376
<i>[pensive music]</i>

02:46.376 --> 02:53.425
<i>♪ ♪</i>

03:11.317 --> 03:15.113
- Oh, man, look at this.
[chuckles]

03:15.113 --> 03:16.322
What's the occasion?

03:18.241 --> 03:21.786
- Since when does a wife
need an occasion to cook

03:21.786 --> 03:23.413
her husband's favorite meal?

03:29.002 --> 03:30.587
- Those didn't come from a box.

03:30.587 --> 03:33.423
- No, sir, they did not.

03:35.508 --> 03:38.386
[utensils clinking]

03:40.472 --> 03:42.765
I want to foster another child.

03:49.063 --> 03:53.985
I have so much extra time now
that I'm not working anymore.

03:53.985 --> 03:56.070
And it's--
it's always been such

03:56.070 --> 03:58.281
a positive experience
in the past.

03:59.699 --> 04:02.285
Christina loves it when
we bring children in,

04:02.285 --> 04:04.287
don't you, sweetheart?

04:04.287 --> 04:07.457
- I guess.
- Yeah.

04:07.457 --> 04:09.375
[utensil clinking]

04:11.252 --> 04:15.131
- New job's got me
working a lot,

04:15.131 --> 04:18.134
traveling more.

04:18.134 --> 04:19.886
Sure it's a good idea?

04:23.348 --> 04:26.267
- We've got so much love
to give in this family.

04:31.731 --> 04:37.946
<i>♪ ♪</i>

04:37.946 --> 04:40.365
ALLAN:
This is delicious, honey.

04:42.742 --> 04:45.245
David, this is Ms. Betty,

04:45.245 --> 04:48.831
and this is
our daughter Christina.

04:48.831 --> 04:51.543
Ladies, this is David.

04:51.543 --> 04:53.461
- Hello, David.

04:58.967 --> 05:02.929
Christina made this for you.
Isn't it beautiful?

05:02.929 --> 05:04.764
Do you know what it says?

05:06.474 --> 05:08.643
- "Welcome David."

05:10.144 --> 05:13.273
BETTY:
Look at you,
what a good reader you are.

05:16.150 --> 05:21.030
David, we are so happy
to have you,

05:21.030 --> 05:25.493
and we just want you
to feel at home here.

05:25.493 --> 05:27.412
- Yes, ma'am.

05:30.873 --> 05:35.295
- Well, Christina, do you want
to show David to his new room?

05:35.295 --> 05:37.672
- Come on.
- There you go.

05:37.672 --> 05:38.923
- Thank you.

05:38.923 --> 05:41.968
<i>[gentle music]</i>

05:41.968 --> 05:47.056
<i>♪ ♪</i>

05:47.056 --> 05:48.641
- He's perfect.

05:52.937 --> 05:56.274
<i>[ominous music]</i>

05:56.274 --> 05:59.277
[shower running]

05:59.277 --> 06:06.242
<i>♪ ♪</i>

06:45.031 --> 06:48.618
<i>[acoustic guitar music]</i>

06:48.618 --> 06:53.623
- ♪ I will enter his gates
with thanksgiving in my heart ♪

06:53.623 --> 06:58.336
♪ I will enter his courts
with praise ♪

06:58.336 --> 07:03.549
♪ I will say this is the day
that the Lord has made ♪

07:03.549 --> 07:08.596
♪ I will rejoice
for he has made me glad ♪

07:08.596 --> 07:13.184
ALL:
♪ He has made me glad,
he has made me glad ♪

07:13.184 --> 07:18.106
♪ I will rejoice
for he has made me glad ♪

07:18.106 --> 07:22.735
♪ He has made me glad,
he has made me glad ♪

07:22.735 --> 07:27.615
♪ I will rejoice
for he has made me glad ♪

07:32.495 --> 07:34.414
BETTY: Bye.
CHURCHGOER: Good night.

07:34.414 --> 07:37.458
CHURCHGOER:
Candy, oh, my goodness,
that was so good.

07:37.458 --> 07:39.502
CANDY: Well, thank you.
CHURCHGOER: Just great.

07:39.502 --> 07:41.921
CANDY: Oh, my gosh, y'all.
CHURCHGOER: That was!

07:41.921 --> 07:44.006
- Thank you so much,
bless y'all.

07:44.006 --> 07:46.467
CHURCHGOER: God bless you.
- See you next week, okay?

07:46.467 --> 07:48.761
Hey, um,
I won't be long, but don't

07:48.761 --> 07:50.263
get the kids
too wound up, okay?

07:50.263 --> 07:52.265
- Who, me?
- Yes, you.

07:52.265 --> 07:56.519
Where's my favorite pastor at?

07:56.519 --> 07:58.646
Pick it up,
you won't put it down.

07:58.646 --> 08:00.773
You have been warned.

08:00.773 --> 08:05.027
Commander Rodney Landa?
Ooh, very commanding.

08:05.027 --> 08:06.362
- Mm-hmm.

08:06.362 --> 08:08.531
[both chuckle]

08:15.121 --> 08:18.249
- All right, come on now.

08:18.249 --> 08:19.459
- What?

08:21.169 --> 08:22.920
- Sweetie...

08:25.381 --> 08:28.885
- Bill and I
are getting divorced.

08:31.304 --> 08:33.181
- Jesus...

08:36.559 --> 08:39.103
Did he cheat?

08:39.103 --> 08:41.397
- No.

08:41.397 --> 08:42.899
[laughs]

08:42.899 --> 08:45.359
No, of course not.
- Okay.

08:47.320 --> 08:48.821
- It's just...

08:51.449 --> 08:53.785
Over.

08:53.785 --> 08:57.789
I woke up one morning thinking,
"Maybe this is it."

08:57.789 --> 09:00.541
Well, not for me.

09:04.962 --> 09:07.882
- You're gonna be fine.

09:07.882 --> 09:09.258
You are fine.

09:09.258 --> 09:11.010
- This is the first time
in a while

09:11.010 --> 09:14.806
I'm kinda excited to see
what's coming next.

09:16.808 --> 09:19.769
- Yeah, all right.

09:19.769 --> 09:22.480
<i>[gentle music]</i>

09:22.480 --> 09:28.653
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:28.653 --> 09:31.656
[television playing
indistinctly]

09:47.088 --> 09:48.548
[record scratches]

09:48.548 --> 09:50.842
[David Soul's
"Don't Give Up On Us" plays]

09:50.842 --> 09:57.140
<i>♪ ♪</i>

09:57.140 --> 09:59.225
DAVID SOUL:
♪ Don't give up on us, baby ♪

09:59.225 --> 10:00.935
[Candy singing along]

10:00.935 --> 10:07.108
♪ Don't make
the wrong seem right ♪

10:07.108 --> 10:10.403
♪ The future isn't
just one night ♪

10:10.403 --> 10:12.363
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:12.363 --> 10:15.491
♪ It's written
in the moonlight ♪

10:15.491 --> 10:17.118
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:17.118 --> 10:19.871
♪ And painted on the stars ♪

10:19.871 --> 10:23.791
♪ We can't change ours ♪

10:23.791 --> 10:25.459
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:25.459 --> 10:29.130
♪ Don't give up on us, baby ♪

10:29.130 --> 10:35.636
♪ We're still
worth one more try ♪

10:35.636 --> 10:39.056
♪ I know we put a last one by ♪

10:39.056 --> 10:40.850
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:40.850 --> 10:44.061
♪ Just for a rainy evening ♪

10:44.061 --> 10:45.521
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:45.521 --> 10:49.483
♪ When maybe stars are few ♪

10:49.483 --> 10:53.196
♪ Don't give up on us, I know ♪

10:53.196 --> 10:57.158
♪ We can still come through ♪

10:57.158 --> 10:59.660
<i>♪ ♪</i>

10:59.660 --> 11:03.873
♪ I really lost
my head last night ♪

11:03.873 --> 11:07.668
♪ You've got a right
to start believing ♪

11:07.668 --> 11:09.295
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:09.295 --> 11:13.716
♪ There's still
a little love left ♪

11:13.716 --> 11:16.552
♪ Even so ♪

11:16.552 --> 11:23.559
<i>♪ ♪</i>

11:23.559 --> 11:26.771
♪ Don't give up on us, baby ♪

11:26.771 --> 11:28.814
<i>- Maybe it all ties together.</i>

11:28.814 --> 11:31.317
<i>- Well, would you like
a few more maybes?</i>

11:31.317 --> 11:33.444
CANDY:
Have you spoken to Bill lately?

11:35.821 --> 11:37.448
PAT:
Bill Richardson?

11:37.448 --> 11:39.116
CANDY:
No, Ponder.

11:40.368 --> 11:43.537
- I ran into him down
McKinney Square last week, why?

11:45.831 --> 11:49.460
- No reason, just wondered why
you two don't hang out more.

11:49.460 --> 11:50.628
- Hmm.

11:52.964 --> 11:56.217
Sundays at church,
I feel sick enough.

12:00.304 --> 12:04.225
- Well, you could use
more friends is all.

12:08.229 --> 12:10.690
- I'm not 11.

12:10.690 --> 12:12.733
I have you.

12:12.733 --> 12:14.318
I have the kids.

12:14.318 --> 12:15.861
That's all the friends I need.

12:15.861 --> 12:16.988
<i>JIM: Do you mind if I
finish this sentence?</i>

12:16.988 --> 12:18.990
<i>RICHIE:
No, I'm sorry, go ahead.</i>

12:18.990 --> 12:20.449
<i>JIM:
I went up
to Tooley's office,</i>

12:20.449 --> 12:26.163
<i>and I found his, uh,
expense sheet and these.</i>

12:26.163 --> 12:27.790
<i>RICHIE:
Glasses?</i>

12:27.790 --> 12:30.418
<i>JIM: Sharp--that's exactly
what I thought they were too.</i>

12:30.418 --> 12:33.129
<i>RICHIE:
No, no,
that's not what I meant.</i>

12:33.129 --> 12:36.090
<i>JIM:
Oh, Joe, what--</i>

12:36.090 --> 12:37.800
<i>what was he doing
on the freeways,</i>

12:37.800 --> 12:38.843
<i>which he was afraid of...</i>

12:38.843 --> 12:41.595
- Come on, it just started.

12:41.595 --> 12:42.847
<i>RICHIE:
Two pair, maybe?</i>

12:42.847 --> 12:44.181
<i>JIM:
No, I called Mary.</i>

12:44.181 --> 12:46.058
<i>He only had one pair.
No others.</i>

12:46.058 --> 12:47.977
<i>RICHIE:
Listen, Mr. Rockford,
we're onto something here,</i>

12:47.977 --> 12:49.270
<i>I can feel it.</i>

12:49.270 --> 12:50.646
<i>Joe Tooley was murdered.</i>

12:50.646 --> 12:52.898
<i>[organ music]</i>

12:52.898 --> 12:57.695
<i>♪ ♪</i>

12:57.695 --> 13:00.031
- Top one?
- Top.

13:00.031 --> 13:01.490
Oh!

13:07.288 --> 13:10.666
SHERRY:
No, when JR said Gary
wasn't smart enough

13:10.666 --> 13:12.668
to want anything...
- I know!

13:12.668 --> 13:14.253
- Strong enough to ask. Whoo!

13:14.253 --> 13:15.796
SANDRA:
And I mean,
it's his own brother!

13:15.796 --> 13:17.131
- I know, right?

13:17.131 --> 13:18.257
LINDA:
Hey, y'all,
I've been thinking about

13:18.257 --> 13:20.051
cutting my hair
like Ms. Ellie's.

13:20.051 --> 13:21.927
It's soft but strong, you know?

13:21.927 --> 13:23.054
It's just
like a little bit shorter.

13:23.054 --> 13:24.388
CANDY:
I love that for you.

13:24.388 --> 13:25.973
I love that for you.

13:25.973 --> 13:27.683
Oh, well, hey there,
Ms. Betty.

13:27.683 --> 13:29.810
BETTY:
Hi, y'all.

13:29.810 --> 13:32.146
So I was thinking
it might be fun

13:32.146 --> 13:34.815
to start up a children's choir.

13:34.815 --> 13:37.026
I know my Christina
would love it.

13:37.026 --> 13:40.446
And, um, now that
we have Davey, you know,

13:40.446 --> 13:43.407
we're fostering
a little boy, Davey.

13:43.407 --> 13:46.160
Poor little thing,
he is just a sweetheart.

13:46.160 --> 13:48.245
But I thought
with all our little ones,

13:48.245 --> 13:51.040
we could put together
something really special.

13:52.583 --> 13:55.211
SHERRY:
Well, aren't you sweet,
Betty?

13:55.211 --> 13:58.172
You--you want to teach
children to be louder?

13:58.172 --> 14:00.966
[laughter]

14:00.966 --> 14:03.969
- No, I want to
teach them to work together

14:03.969 --> 14:06.806
in harmony
towards a common goal.

14:06.806 --> 14:13.270
<i>♪ ♪</i>

14:14.855 --> 14:16.899
- Well, I think it's
a wonderful idea, I do.

14:16.899 --> 14:20.444
- I think the kids would
enjoy it, and, uh,

14:20.444 --> 14:22.738
it'd be a good way for Davey
to make some friends.

14:22.738 --> 14:25.157
So, um,
something to think about.

14:27.076 --> 14:28.619
- We sure will!

14:28.619 --> 14:30.454
- See you in there.
BETTY: All right.

14:32.164 --> 14:35.209
- Ugh, St. Betty
of perpetual distress.

14:35.209 --> 14:37.336
- Ugh, God, you're awful!

14:37.336 --> 14:40.005
- What? I said she was sweet.

14:40.005 --> 14:42.216
- She's just trying
to do a good thing.

14:42.216 --> 14:43.801
LINDA:
She took in
that poor little boy,

14:43.801 --> 14:45.344
isn't that enough good to do?

14:45.344 --> 14:48.430
- Oh, honey, it is a long road
to hoe for moral superiority.

14:48.430 --> 14:51.016
She's just trying to make us
feel like we don't do enough.

14:51.016 --> 14:53.394
- Well, we don't.
You definitely don't.

14:53.394 --> 14:54.520
SHERRY:
Speak for yourself.

14:54.520 --> 14:57.523
[indistinct chatter]

15:13.706 --> 15:15.332
- She's running behind.

15:21.630 --> 15:22.798
- Good morning, everybody.

15:24.592 --> 15:26.302
ALL:
Good morning.

15:26.302 --> 15:27.595
- Bet you're all wondering
why you're seeing

15:27.595 --> 15:29.054
my pretty face up here
on a Sunday morning.

15:29.054 --> 15:30.472
[crowd chuckling]

15:30.472 --> 15:32.099
Don't bother ducking,
I won't be up here long enough

15:32.099 --> 15:33.976
for the ceiling
to come down on me.

15:33.976 --> 15:37.605
[audience laughs]

15:37.605 --> 15:39.190
Thank you.
- Oh, boy.

15:39.190 --> 15:41.567
DON:
Uh, first off,
Jackie's fine, folks.

15:41.567 --> 15:45.529
Uh, she's just taking care
of some--some personal issues.

15:45.529 --> 15:48.282
Um...

15:48.282 --> 15:50.451
she and Bill
are getting divorced.

15:50.451 --> 15:52.536
PAT: What?
- Yeah.

15:52.536 --> 15:54.955
[people murmuring]

15:54.955 --> 15:58.918
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

15:58.918 --> 16:01.587
DON:
Yeah, I know.

16:01.587 --> 16:04.006
Well,
since there's not gonna be

16:04.006 --> 16:09.220
a proper sermon today,
I think we should all go

16:09.220 --> 16:12.556
spend the day doing what--
what makes us happy.

16:12.556 --> 16:15.768
Maybe go see that, uh,
<i>Grease</i> again.

16:15.768 --> 16:17.311
That was a hoot and holler!

16:18.687 --> 16:21.774
Ah, but--but it makes
you think--it makes you think.

16:21.774 --> 16:23.108
Right from the beginning,

16:23.108 --> 16:24.818
there's two ways
of telling every story.

16:27.446 --> 16:29.281
<i>[organ music]</i>

16:29.281 --> 16:31.909
<i>♪ ♪</i>

16:31.909 --> 16:33.369
- Poor Jackie.

16:33.369 --> 16:34.828
- She's fine.

16:34.828 --> 16:36.372
- How do you know?
- You knew about this?

16:36.372 --> 16:38.207
- It wasn't mine to tell.

16:38.207 --> 16:40.000
- Is there another woman?
- No.

16:40.000 --> 16:42.211
- Another man.
- No.

16:42.211 --> 16:43.671
- Divorce, I would never...

16:43.671 --> 16:45.923
- I would
have to just leave town!

16:45.923 --> 16:48.467
- They grew apart,
okay, it happens.

16:48.467 --> 16:50.552
- Not around here, it doesn't.
- Mm-mm.

16:50.552 --> 16:53.430
- Except for her.

16:53.430 --> 16:56.767
CANDY:
Hey, y'all!

16:56.767 --> 16:58.644
- People are gonna talk.

16:58.644 --> 17:01.814
- I gotta go.
- Okay.

17:01.814 --> 17:05.109
SHERRY: See you next week.
- Bye. Bye.

17:05.109 --> 17:07.653
- You coming?
- Oh, yeah.

17:07.653 --> 17:10.656
[utensils clinking]

17:12.491 --> 17:14.243
- Mmm.

17:19.790 --> 17:22.293
That was good.

17:22.293 --> 17:24.378
Back later.

17:24.378 --> 17:26.755
BETTY:
Where are you going?

17:26.755 --> 17:29.049
- Thursday--volleyball.

17:31.552 --> 17:34.471
- Of course, um, have fun.

17:34.471 --> 17:35.764
ALLAN:
Thanks, honey!

17:35.764 --> 17:38.100
CHRISTINA: Bye, Daddy!
ALLAN: Bye!

17:38.100 --> 17:41.437
<i>[apprehensive music]</i>

17:41.437 --> 17:48.027
<i>♪ ♪</i>

18:08.922 --> 18:12.176
- There you are.
What you doing?

18:12.176 --> 18:15.262
- Becky threw it out the window
to see if it could fly.

18:15.262 --> 18:18.098
I told the guys
it looks like an owl.

18:19.642 --> 18:21.894
- Well, I'm off to volleyball.

18:21.894 --> 18:25.272
- Oh, I'll round up
the munchkins.

18:25.272 --> 18:27.149
CANDY:
No, no, no, stay here.

18:27.149 --> 18:29.026
- Oh, no, come on,
we love watching you play.

18:29.026 --> 18:31.612
- Well, you do, but the kids
just run around like maniacs,

18:31.612 --> 18:34.281
so let's not show everyone
what terrible parents we are.

18:35.866 --> 18:39.578
- Okay, you sure?
- I mean it, I'm sure--stay.

18:39.578 --> 18:41.121
PAT: Love you.
CANDY: Love you!

18:41.121 --> 18:45.125
<i>[disco music]</i>

18:45.125 --> 18:49.046
SINGER:
♪ Jump, jump, jump on it ♪

18:49.046 --> 18:51.131
PLAYER: That's it.
Oh, oh, we gotta go for it.

18:51.131 --> 18:53.300
CANDY: Oh, yeah.
COACH: Okay, up--good.

18:53.300 --> 18:55.219
Good, Sherry, Candy.

18:55.219 --> 18:56.637
PLAYER: Oh!
PLAYER: Oh!

18:56.637 --> 18:59.390
[all cheering]

18:59.390 --> 19:01.934
CANDY: All right, come on.
COACH: There you go, over!

19:01.934 --> 19:04.103
PLAYER: Get it, get it, get it!
[screams]

19:04.103 --> 19:06.313
PLAYER:
Oh, sorry!

19:06.313 --> 19:08.482
CANDY:
Shake it off.

19:08.482 --> 19:09.858
All right, team,
let's go--whoo!

19:09.858 --> 19:12.403
COACH:
Game point, game point!

19:12.403 --> 19:16.115
SINGER:
♪ Jump on it and ride ♪

19:16.115 --> 19:19.576
♪ Jump, jump, jump on it ♪

19:19.576 --> 19:20.786
♪ Jump, jump... ♪

19:20.786 --> 19:24.123
[all cheering]

19:24.123 --> 19:26.417
COACH:
All right, okay--okay.

19:26.417 --> 19:29.753
PLAYER:
That was hard!

19:29.753 --> 19:33.298
CANDY:
Ugh, holy cow, my hamstrings.

19:33.298 --> 19:35.092
ALLAN:
Oh, you oughta think
about getting

19:35.092 --> 19:38.679
some new shoes, then,
with a better grip on 'em.

19:38.679 --> 19:40.347
I was poking around
Sears the other day,

19:40.347 --> 19:42.474
and I saw they had
the new Winner IIs.

19:42.474 --> 19:44.935
It's good shoe,
33% off, good deal.

19:44.935 --> 19:46.228
Thinking about gettin'
'em myself.

19:46.228 --> 19:48.730
- Oh, yeah?
Sounds like a good deal.

19:48.730 --> 19:52.317
ALLAN: [groans]
Get some water. Oh...

