40:11.911 --> 40:15.498
I didn't think it was going to,
but then it did.

40:15.498 --> 40:18.960
I like trying to guess
what the rhyme's gonna be, so.

40:18.960 --> 40:21.337
This one really threw me
for a loop.

40:23.130 --> 40:25.841
- Yeah, she's really good.

40:25.841 --> 40:27.885
- Yeah.
- Mm-hmm.

40:27.885 --> 40:29.553
Yeah.

40:29.553 --> 40:30.721
Hmm.

40:30.721 --> 40:33.224
- Okay,
I'm gonna get a jog in.

40:33.224 --> 40:34.350
- Okay.

40:41.691 --> 40:45.569
[phone rings]

40:45.569 --> 40:47.113
- Hello?

40:47.113 --> 40:50.324
- So tell me again why I'm not
supposed to have an affair.

40:50.324 --> 40:53.744
<i>JACKIE:
Candy, because you have
a wonderful life</i>

40:53.744 --> 40:56.205
<i>and you don't want
to blow it up.</i>

40:56.205 --> 40:57.790
- But I wouldn't.

41:00.042 --> 41:01.794
- That's what they all say.

41:03.421 --> 41:06.340
- It would just be
for a little distraction,

41:06.340 --> 41:10.261
some spice, I mean, why not?

41:10.261 --> 41:14.140
- Feelings will happen,
they always do.

41:14.140 --> 41:16.892
<i>CANDY:
But they don't have to.</i>

41:16.892 --> 41:21.605
JACKIE:
I don't know,
that's not what I see.

41:21.605 --> 41:25.401
- He just sits here,
mouth breathing on the couch.

41:25.401 --> 41:27.403
I mean, don't I deserve
more than that?

41:29.697 --> 41:31.073
[car door slams]

41:40.541 --> 41:42.710
[car door slams]

41:42.710 --> 41:45.588
[engine turns over]

41:48.966 --> 41:52.636
<i>[melancholy music]</i>

41:52.636 --> 41:59.643
<i>♪ ♪</i>

42:21.499 --> 42:23.000
[garage door clatters]

42:35.638 --> 42:37.348
BETTY:
What did they say?

42:40.518 --> 42:42.144
- It's fine.

42:44.355 --> 42:46.398
They said it happens
a lot, so...

42:49.276 --> 42:50.903
Bad fit.

42:55.783 --> 42:57.243
- You must think I'm a monster.

42:57.243 --> 43:00.037
- Bets, cut it out.

43:02.039 --> 43:05.793
When someone is troubled,
it's hard to take care of them.

43:05.793 --> 43:07.545
You did your best.

43:11.257 --> 43:14.260
BETTY:
You're going
to volleyball tonight?

43:14.260 --> 43:15.845
ALLAN:
I missed one practice already.

43:15.845 --> 43:17.388
You know they count on me.

43:20.057 --> 43:21.892
- Don't go.

43:21.892 --> 43:23.978
- Was Davey sad?

43:25.229 --> 43:28.065
- No, he's gonna be fine,
sweetheart.

43:28.065 --> 43:30.818
They're gonna make sure to find
just the perfect home for him.

43:32.194 --> 43:34.113
Take care of your mom
while I'm at practice.

43:34.113 --> 43:36.740
CHRISTINA:
We can watch <i>Mork & Mindy,</i> Mom.

43:36.740 --> 43:38.367
- Oh, nano-nano.

43:38.367 --> 43:45.374
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:12.693 --> 44:16.030
Service!

44:16.030 --> 44:18.699
<i>[pensive music]</i>

44:18.699 --> 44:22.161
<i>♪ ♪</i>

44:22.161 --> 44:23.579
[cheering]

44:23.579 --> 44:25.331
- No feet, y'all, no feet.

44:27.917 --> 44:29.376
Ugh!

44:29.376 --> 44:30.502
PLAYER:
One more.

44:30.502 --> 44:32.004
What'd you say
about no feet, Candy?

44:32.004 --> 44:34.632
- Two can be pissed off,
so what if you are.

44:34.632 --> 44:35.883
PLAYER:
All right,
you two, break it up!

44:35.883 --> 44:37.551
PLAYER:
Come on!

44:43.849 --> 44:45.893
- You got it. You got it!

44:45.893 --> 44:52.900
<i>♪ ♪</i>

45:21.303 --> 45:23.222
[cheering and clapping]

45:23.222 --> 45:24.807
- Nice!

45:51.500 --> 45:54.503
[engine grinding]

45:59.174 --> 46:01.468
ALLAN:
Hey, Candy.

46:01.468 --> 46:03.137
- Please don't say anything
or I'm never

46:03.137 --> 46:05.723
gonna get this out.

46:05.723 --> 46:07.933
But I find you

46:07.933 --> 46:10.352
attractive...

46:10.352 --> 46:13.480
and, well,
I'd like to have an affair.

46:18.861 --> 46:22.406
Okay, well, good night, Allan.

46:36.378 --> 46:37.838
[car door thumps shut]

46:45.804 --> 46:48.807
<i>[unsettling music]</i>

46:48.807 --> 46:50.601
<i>♪ ♪</i>

46:50.601 --> 46:53.896
<i>DON:
Candace, what did you do then?</i>

46:53.896 --> 47:00.611
<i>♪ ♪</i>

47:03.947 --> 47:05.824
- I grabbed the axe.
